# Notes
## Types of Orders (at the Exchange)
* Symbol
* Buy, Sell
* Market, Limit
* Shares
* Price (if Limit)

## The Order Book (recap)
<pre>
* Ask	$100.10	  100
* Ask	$100.05	  500
* Ask	$100.00  1000
* Bid	 $99.95	  100
* Bid	 $99.90	   50
* Bid	 $99.85	   50
</pre>

## How Brokers Connected to Exchanges


## Types of Orders (with your Broker)
* Additional possibilities:
** Sell short (to open)
** Buy (to close)
* More complex orders (stop limit)

## Mechanics of Short Selling
* Borrow the shares
* Sell them
* You now have:
** Asset: Cash
** Liability: Shares owed

